The paper deals with the problem of computing a minimum weight two edge connected spanning subgraph in a distributed setting. This problem is related to network design and has applications in computer networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and graph theory, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AL (Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the problem involves communication networks, which could place it in cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
